# Uninstall

```bash
sudo apt-get purge ruby
sudo apt-get purge jekyll
# if which github-pages
sudo apt-get purge github-pages
```
#Install

## Ruby  
linux repos are outdated, use rvmfor latest

```bash
curl -L https://get.rvm.io | bash -s stable --autolibs=enabled --ruby

rvm install ruby --latest
```
* grab installed version from cli output
* enable *un command as login shell* option in gnome-terminal: https://rvm.io/integration/gnome-terminal
* start new terminal session

```bash
rvm use <version> --default
```

## Jekyll

```bash
gem install jekyll --no-rdoc --no-ri

```

## github-pages

```bash
gem install github-pages --no-rdoc --no-ri
```
